The paper proposes a novel variational-recurrent imputation network for electronic health records (EHR) datasets. The method leverages deep generative models and recurrent networks to handle the sparsity, irregularity, and high-dimensionality of EHR data, as well as the uncertainty in missing value estimates. This work involves machine learning, deep learning, and natural language processing techniques, which are commonly associated with the arXiv CS sub-categories of cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.NE.
